<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>FAQ | Hustle Property</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/styles.css">
</head>
<body class="page-bg page-bg--faq">

  <header class="property-public-hero property-public-hero--contact">
    <a href="/" class="property-public-hero__back">← Back to listings</a>
    <div class="property-public-hero__brand">
      <div class="property-public-logo-panel">
        <a href="/" class="property-public-logo-link" aria-label="Hustle Property — home">
          <img src="/logo.png" alt="Hustle Property" class="property-public-logo" width="200" height="auto" decoding="async">
        </a>
      </div>
      <p class="property-public-hero__subtitle">Frequently asked questions</p>
    </div>
  </header>

  <main class="content-wrap faq-page-main">
    <section class="form-card faq-page-card" aria-labelledby="faq-heading">
      <h1 id="faq-heading" class="faq-page__title">FAQ</h1>
      <p class="faq-page__lead">Quick answers about industrial and commercial listings in Cape Town. For anything specific, <a href="/contact">contact us</a>.</p>

      <div class="faq-list">
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__q">Which areas do you focus on?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__a">
            <p>We work across Cape Town industrial and commercial nodes, with a strong presence in areas such as Maitland, Paarden Eiland, Epping, and nearby locations. Use the <strong>Area</strong> filter on the homepage to narrow listings.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__q">How do I arrange a viewing?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__a">
            <p>Use the enquiry form on any listing, <a href="/contact">contact us</a> directly, or reach out on WhatsApp or phone. We’ll confirm availability and coordinate access with landlords where needed.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__q">What does “To Let” and “For Sale” mean on a listing?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__a">
            <p><strong>To Let</strong> means the space is available on a lease basis. <strong>For Sale</strong> means ownership is on offer. Some stock may be marketed both ways; the status on the card reflects how we are currently promoting it.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__q">Are sizes and rentals on the website final?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__a">
            <p>Sizes and asking rentals are based on what is on file and may be approximate or subject to update. We’ll confirm the latest figures, inclusions, and landlord conditions before you commit to an offer.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__q">Do you work with tenants and buyers only, or landlords too?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__a">
            <p>We act for landlords and developers as well as tenants and purchasers. If you need to let or sell industrial or commercial space, get in touch to discuss an appropriate mandate and marketing plan.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__q">How quickly will someone respond to my enquiry?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__a">
            <p>We aim to respond promptly during business hours. If your need is urgent, include that in your message or use WhatsApp or phone so we can prioritise.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
        <details class="faq-item">
          <summary class="faq-item__q">What is the “Done deals” page?</summary>
          <div class="faq-item__a">
            <p>It’s a public summary of confirmed transactions and track-record highlights — useful context for the kind of work we do. It doesn’t list every deal or replace tailored advice for your situation.</p>
          </div>
        </details>
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>

</body>
</html>
